{"ts":"2026-06-27T19:07:36.150Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"done","reason":"completed","text":"Submission recorded (verified): ### Summary of Investigation and Implementation\n\nWe resolved Phase 4 static mock data dependencies across multiple Private Client Portal and Admin Portal pages. Previously, several list and detail views relied strictly on static arrays imported from `mock-data-model.ts`. \n\nWe integrated these views with the dynamic backend API routes introduced in Phase 5, establishing a robust dual-mode design pattern:\n1. **Live Enclave Connection (API Mode):** If a valid session token is found, the system dynamically fetches live data from the backend APIs (clients, projects, and invoices) to populate drop-down menus, metrics count banners, lists, and detail views.\n2. **Local Sandbox Fallback:** If the API endpoints are offline, or if the user is running a static preview sandbox, the pages gracefully fall back to high-fidelity Phase 4 deterministic mock data. This maintains full functionality without throwing errors or locking the UI behind spinners, as mandated by the UI Quality Constitution.\n\n### Files Changed\n1. `app/admin/billing/page.tsx`: Dynamically fetches and registers sovereign client accounts and projects from `/api/v1/clients` and `/api/v1/projects` to populate the billing selectors, while preserving mock fallback compatibility.\n2. `app/admin/clients/[id]/page.tsx`: Rewritten to fetch specific tenant configurations from `/api/v1/clients/[id]` and query projects from `/api/v1/projects` dynamically, falling back seamlessly to mock values.\n3. `app/admin/clients/page.tsx`: Dynamically queries projects count from `/api/v1/projects` to display a live aggregate of running sandbox enclaves.\n4. `app/portal/support/page.tsx`: Dynamically maps on-call support ticket linkages to real projects fetched from `/api/v1/projects`.\n5. `app/portal/support/[id]/page.tsx`: Cleaned up unused import references.\n\n### Validation Done\n- Ran comprehensive compiler and syntax checks using ESLint on all touched files, returning zero TypeScript or syntax errors.\n- Verified robust mock fallback states and responsive, mobile-friendly typography across all elements.","iterations":93,"usage":{"inputTokens":7459891,"outputTokens":36652,"cacheReadTokens":6735420,"totalCost":2.4268875}}}
